hpnicfEvi.name: hpnicfEvi

revisions.description: HPN-ICF-EVI-MIB module for managing EVI-capable switches.

hpnicfEvi.description: This MIB contains the objects for managing Ethernet Virtual Interconnect(EVI).

HpnicfEviMacType.name: HpnicfEviMacType
HpnicfEviMacType.description: MAC addresses include three types: dynamic, static, and flood (MACs configured for selective flooding).

hpnicfEviDesignatedVlan.name: hpnicfEviDesignatedVlan
hpnicfEviDesignatedVlan.description: The designated VLAN is used for edge devices on a multihomed site to exchange EVI IS-IS hello packets for DED election and extended-VLAN assignment.

hpnicfEviSiteID.name: hpnicfEviSiteID
hpnicfEviSiteID.description: Site ID. The edge devices in the same site must have the same site ID.

hpnicfEviIfExtendVlanTable.name: hpnicfEviIfExtendVlanTable
hpnicfEviIfExtendVlanTable.description: A table that contains extended VLAN entries. A site extends extended VLANs to remote sites over an EVI tunnel.

hpnicfEviIfExtendVlanEntry.name: hpnicfEviIfExtendVlanEntry
hpnicfEviIfExtendVlanEntry.description: Detailed information about each extended VLAN.

hpnicfEviIfExtendVlanIndex.name: hpnicfEviIfExtendVlanIndex
hpnicfEviIfExtendVlanIndex.description: Each VLAN index specifies a VLAN ID in the range of 1 to 4094.

hpnicfEviIfExtendVlanLAV.name: hpnicfEviIfExtendVlanLAV
hpnicfEviIfExtendVlanLAV.description: Local Active VLANs (LAVs), which are active VLANs on the EVI tunnel interface. The interface can extend only active VLANs to remote sites.

hpnicfEviIfVlanMappingTable.name: hpnicfEviIfVlanMappingTable
hpnicfEviIfVlanMappingTable.description: VLAN mapping table on the interface.

hpnicfEviIfVlanMappingEntry.name: hpnicfEviIfVlanMappingEntry
hpnicfEviIfVlanMappingEntry.description: Detailed information about each VLAN mapping.

hpnicfEviIfVlanMappingSiteId.name: hpnicfEviIfVlanMappingSiteId
hpnicfEviIfVlanMappingSiteId.description: Site ID of the interface on which the VLAN mapping is configured. If '0' is specified, the operation applies to all sites.

hpnicfEviIfVlanMappingSrc.name: hpnicfEviIfVlanMappingSrc
hpnicfEviIfVlanMappingSrc.description: Local VLAN ID in the mapping.

hpnicfEviIfVlanMappingDst.name: hpnicfEviIfVlanMappingDst
hpnicfEviIfVlanMappingDst.description: Remote VLAN ID in the mapping.

hpnicfEviIfAttributeTable.name: hpnicfEviIfAttributeTable
hpnicfEviIfAttributeTable.description: A table that contains EVI tunnel attribute entries.

hpnicfEviIfAttributeEntry.name: hpnicfEviIfAttributeEntry
hpnicfEviIfAttributeEntry.description: Detailed information about the attributes of each EVI tunnel.

hpnicfEviIfFloodingMode.name: hpnicfEviIfFloodingMode
hpnicfEviIfFloodingMode.description: State of the EVI flooding function. The function is enabled if the value is set to true.

hpnicfEviIfARPSuppression.name: hpnicfEviIfARPSuppression
hpnicfEviIfARPSuppression.description: State of the ARP flooding suppression function. The function is enabled if the value is set to true.

hpnicfEviIfFloodingMacTable.name: hpnicfEviIfFloodingMacTable
hpnicfEviIfFloodingMacTable.description: A table that contains MAC addresses configured for selective flooding.

hpnicfEviIfFloodingMacEntry.name: hpnicfEviIfFloodingMacEntry
hpnicfEviIfFloodingMacEntry.description: Detailed information about each MAC address used for EVI selective flooding.

hpnicfEviIfFloodingMacAddress.name: hpnicfEviIfFloodingMacAddress
hpnicfEviIfFloodingMacAddress.description: MAC address used for EVI selective flooding.

hpnicfEviIfFloodMacVlanIndex.name: hpnicfEviIfFloodMacVlanIndex
hpnicfEviIfFloodMacVlanIndex.description: The VLAN that contains the MAC address.

hpnicfEviIfFloodingMacRowStatus.name: hpnicfEviIfFloodingMacRowStatus
hpnicfEviIfFloodingMacRowStatus.description: State of the MAC address entry. You can use this object to create or delete entries. Deleting entries does not delete this object.

hpnicfEviMacCountTable.name: hpnicfEviMacCountTable
hpnicfEviMacCountTable.description: EVI MAC statistics table. The table contains MAC entry counts sorted by MAC address types, including local MACs, local MAC conflicts, remote MACs, and remote MAC conflicts.

hpnicfEviMacLocalConflicts.name: hpnicfEviMacLocalConflicts
hpnicfEviMacLocalConflicts.description: Number of local MACs that conflict with remote MACs.

hpnicfEviMacRemoteMacs.name: hpnicfEviMacRemoteMacs
hpnicfEviMacRemoteMacs.description: Number of remote MACs received from remote edge devices.

hpnicfEviMacRemoteConflicts.name: hpnicfEviMacRemoteConflicts
hpnicfEviMacRemoteConflicts.description: Number of remote MACs that conflict with local MACs.

hpnicfEviMacLocalTable.name: hpnicfEviMacLocalTable
hpnicfEviMacLocalTable.description: MAC address table that only contains MAC addresses at the site.

hpnicfEviMacLocalEntry.name: hpnicfEviMacLocalEntry
hpnicfEviMacLocalEntry.description: Detailed informaiton about each local MAC entry.

hpnicfEviMacLocalVlan.name: hpnicfEviMacLocalVlan
hpnicfEviMacLocalVlan.description: VLANs that contain the local MACs.

hpnicfEviMacLocalMacType.name: hpnicfEviMacLocalMacType
hpnicfEviMacLocalMacType.description: MAC address types, including: dynamic MACs, static MACs, and flood MACs (MACs configured for selective flooding).

hpnicfEviMacLocalConflict.name: hpnicfEviMacLocalConflict
hpnicfEviMacLocalConflict.description: Whether the MAC conflicts with any remote MAC.

hpnicfEviMacRemoteTable.name: hpnicfEviMacRemoteTable
hpnicfEviMacRemoteTable.description: A table contains MAC addresses received from remote edge devices.

hpnicfEviMacRemoteEntry.name: hpnicfEviMacRemoteEntry
hpnicfEviMacRemoteEntry.description: Detailed information about each remote MAC.

hpnicfEviMacRemoteVlan.name: hpnicfEviMacRemoteVlan
hpnicfEviMacRemoteVlan.description: VLANs that contain remote MAC addresses.

hpnicfEviMacRemoteMacEffect.name: hpnicfEviMacRemoteMacEffect
hpnicfEviMacRemoteMacEffect.description: Whether the MAC can be used for forwarding traffic.

hpnicfEviMacRemoteConflict.name: hpnicfEviMacRemoteConflict
hpnicfEviMacRemoteConflict.description: The remote MAC conflicts with a local MAC.

hpnicfEviProcessPolicyTable.name: hpnicfEviProcessPolicyTable
hpnicfEviProcessPolicyTable.description: A table that contains routing policy information for each EVI IS-IS process.

hpnicfEviProcessPolicyEntry.name: hpnicfEviProcessPolicyEntry
hpnicfEviProcessPolicyEntry.description: Detailed information about the routing policy for each EVI IS-IS process.

hpnicfEviProcessPolicy.name: hpnicfEviProcessPolicy
hpnicfEviProcessPolicy.description: Routing policy for the EVI IS-IS process.

hpnicfEviProcessGrTable.name: hpnicfEviProcessGrTable
hpnicfEviProcessGrTable.description: A table that contains graceful restart (GR) information.

hpnicfEviProcessGrEntry.name: hpnicfEviProcessGrEntry
hpnicfEviProcessGrEntry.description: Detailed GR information for each EVI IS-IS process.

hpnicfEviProcessGrEnable.name: hpnicfEviProcessGrEnable
hpnicfEviProcessGrEnable.description: Whether the GR function is enabled.

hpnicfEviProcessGrInterval.name: hpnicfEviProcessGrInterval
hpnicfEviProcessGrInterval.description: EVI IS-IS GR interval in the range of 30 to 1800, in seconds.

hpnicfEviProcessVSysTable.name: hpnicfEviProcessVSysTable
hpnicfEviProcessVSysTable.description: A table that contains virtual system entries. Virtual systems are associated with EVI IS-IS processes.

hpnicfEviProcessVSysEntry.name: hpnicfEviProcessVSysEntry
hpnicfEviProcessVSysEntry.description: Detailed information about each vitual system.

hpnicfEviVirtualSysId.name: hpnicfEviVirtualSysId
hpnicfEviVirtualSysId.description: Virtual system ID in hexadecimal notation. The virtual system ID must be unique in the EVI network.

hpnicfEviISISNbrSummaryEntry.name: hpnicfEviISISNbrSummaryEntry
hpnicfEviISISNbrSummaryEntry.description: EVI neighbor statistics table entries. The entries contain the EVI neighbor summary for each EVI IS-IS process.

hpnicfEviISISNbrMaxMultiHomes.name: hpnicfEviISISNbrMaxMultiHomes
hpnicfEviISISNbrMaxMultiHomes.description: The maximum number of edge devices that the site can contain.

hpnicfEviISISNbrSiteNbrs.name: hpnicfEviISISNbrSiteNbrs
hpnicfEviISISNbrSiteNbrs.description: The count of neighbors that belong to the same site.

hpnicfEviISISNbrLinkNbrs.name: hpnicfEviISISNbrLinkNbrs
hpnicfEviISISNbrLinkNbrs.description: The count of neighbors that are in remote sites.

hpnicfEviISISNbrTable.name: hpnicfEviISISNbrTable
hpnicfEviISISNbrTable.description: A table that contains generic information about all neighbors.

hpnicfEviISISNbrEntry.name: hpnicfEviISISNbrEntry
hpnicfEviISISNbrEntry.description: Detailed information about each neighbor of the edge device.

hpnicfEviEnableTable.name: hpnicfEviEnableTable
hpnicfEviEnableTable.description: A table that contains all EVI-enabled neighboring ports of the edge device.

hpnicfEviEnableEntry.name: hpnicfEviEnableEntry
hpnicfEviEnableEntry.description: Detailed information about each EVI-enabled port in the EVI network.

hpnicfEviEnableStatus.name: hpnicfEviEnableStatus
hpnicfEviEnableStatus.description: End station service disable (trunk port) bit. When this bit is set (true), all native frames received on the port and all native frames that would have been sent on the port are discarded. The value of this object MUST be retained across reinitializations of the management system.

hpnicfEviNbrBaseTable.name: hpnicfEviNbrBaseTable
hpnicfEviNbrBaseTable.description: A table that contains basic information about the EVI Neighbor Discovery Protocol (ENDP).

hpnicfEviNbrBaseEntry.name: hpnicfEviNbrBaseEntry
hpnicfEviNbrBaseEntry.description: Detailed information about ENDP for each EVI tunnel.

hpnicfEviNbrSelfServerStatus.name: hpnicfEviNbrSelfServerStatus
hpnicfEviNbrSelfServerStatus.description: If the value is set to true, the EVI neighbor discovery server (ENDS) is enabled. When you enable ENDS on an EVI tunnel interface, an EVI neighbor discovery client (ENDC) on the EVI tunnel interface is also enabled automatically, with the source address of the EVI tunnel as the server address.

hpnicfEviNbrAuthPassword.name: hpnicfEviNbrAuthPassword
hpnicfEviNbrAuthPassword.description: ENDP authentication key. It is a zero-length string when being read.

hpnicfEviNbrClientRegisterInterval.name: hpnicfEviNbrClientRegisterInterval
hpnicfEviNbrClientRegisterInterval.description: Interval at which the ENDCs on an EVI tunnel interface update their registration with their ENDSs.

hpnicfEviNbrRemoteServerTable.name: hpnicfEviNbrRemoteServerTable
hpnicfEviNbrRemoteServerTable.description: A table that contains basic information about the remote ENDSs.

hpnicfEviNbrRemoteServerEntry.name: hpnicfEviNbrRemoteServerEntry
hpnicfEviNbrRemoteServerEntry.description: Detailed information about each remote ENDS. When you set the address of a remote ENDS on an EVI tunnel interface, an ENDC is enabled automatically on the EVI tunnel interface.

hpnicfEviNbrRemoteServerType.name: hpnicfEviNbrRemoteServerType
hpnicfEviNbrRemoteServerType.description: Address type of the remote ENDS, including ipv4 and ipv6.

hpnicfEviNbrRemoteServer.name: hpnicfEviNbrRemoteServer
hpnicfEviNbrRemoteServer.description: Address of the remote ENDS. The address type is specified by the hpnicfEviNbrRemoteServerType object. Address length (4 or 16 bytes) must be consistent with the address type.

hpnicfEviNbrRemoteServerRowStatus.name: hpnicfEviNbrRemoteServerRowStatus
hpnicfEviNbrRemoteServerRowStatus.description: Entry status. This object is used to create or delete entries. Deleting entries does not delete this object.

hpnicfEviNbrTable.name: hpnicfEviNbrTable
hpnicfEviNbrTable.description: A table that contains basic information about neighbors discovered with ENDP.

hpnicfEviNbrEntry.name: hpnicfEviNbrEntry
hpnicfEviNbrEntry.description: Detailed information about each EVI neighbor.

hpnicfEviNbrAddressType.name: hpnicfEviNbrAddressType
hpnicfEviNbrAddressType.description: Address type of the neighbor, including ipv4 and ipv6.

hpnicfEviNbrAddress.name: hpnicfEviNbrAddress
hpnicfEviNbrAddress.description: Address of the neighbor. The address type is specified by the hpnicfEviNbrAddressType object. Address length (4 or 16 bytes) must be consistent with the address type.

hpnicfEviNewDed.name: hpnicfEviNewDed
hpnicfEviNewDed.description: Notifies that a new DED has been elected.

hpnicfEviSiteEDTopoChange.name: hpnicfEviSiteEDTopoChange
hpnicfEviSiteEDTopoChange.description: Notifies that the EVI network topology has changed.

hpnicfEviEDLinkDisconnect.name: hpnicfEviEDLinkDisconnect
hpnicfEviEDLinkDisconnect.description: Notifies that all the EVI links on a tunnel are down.
